    "what_description": "Ruellia macrantha is a perennial herbaceous plant that belongs to the family Acanthaceae. It has erect stems, 60-120 cm tall, with quadrangular, pubescent branches and opposite, elliptical leaves, 5-10 cm long and 2-4 cm wide. The inflorescence is a terminal spike, bearing tubular, purple flowers, 2.5-3.5 cm long, with a 2-lipped corolla, and four stamens. The plant produces four-winged, quadrangular capsules, 4-6 cm long, containing many seeds. Ruellia macrantha is native to Mexico and Central America.",
