    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Ruellia macrantha are tea, tincture, infusion, salve, and decoction, which are made from the plant's leaves and flowers. Tea is prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water to treat fever, sore throat, and digestive issues. Tincture is made by steeping the leaves in ethanol to enhance its bioavailability and is used to treat respiratory issues and fever. Infusion is prepared by steeping the flowers in hot water to treat coughs and sore throats. Decoction is made by boiling the leaves in water to treat digestive issues and salve is prepared by infusing the leaves in oil to treat skin irritations and wounds.",
